node.title: The most important thing to grow your business

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bashar J Katou on September 09, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou, and @bjkuniversity. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'SOCIALLY DISTANCE YOURSELF FROM THESE 5 TYPES OF PEOPLE IN 2022: (SWIPE LEFT) @basharjkatou'.

node.text:
STAY AWAY from these people.

The people you hang out with and surround you influence you.

So, learn to distance yourself from people who don’t take you seriously and tear you down.

It’s not always easy, especially if these people are life-long friends or family members.

But ultimately this is your life and you owe it to yourself to be successful.

Watch out for these 5 types of people and distance yourself from them.

And if you are looking for a community of supportive people…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

(Idea: @steven)

node.text:
THIS will change your life!

What you think defines the quality of your life. 

That’s why a few, seemingly simple mindset shifts can change your life.

Your mindset is a skill in itself and you can learn to change your thinking for the better.

Implement these 7 mindset shifts in your life and see what happens.

And if you want to adopt the mindset of a successful business owner…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity

node.text:
“So if you’re telling me this, are you not rich?” or

“What are you talking about, it’s all I ever see on Instagram nowadays” or

“Reading it again is a waste of time” or

“How are we supposed to learn those secrets? Why would anyone reveal secrets to random people on the internet?”

Here’s my answer:

It’s a little bit like magic. Magicians only reveal tricks to other magicians, because:

Laymen would only spoil the fun but never perform the trick. They would ruin the magic for those who want to enjoy it.

But if no magician can share with laymen- where do the new magicians come from?

So I’m one of the naughty ones who reveal a trick or two, so you can join us.

If you see it everywhere- good for you, it’s a message you don’t get from reading it once.

Believing you get every bit of information from one read is arrogant and prevents you from learning.

That’s why rich people don’t like to share this with people: Most people don’t get it, become cynical and sarcastic and we don’t want to waste time with a naysayer who doesn’t get it.

Just like magicians don’t want to discuss tricks with people who say “magnets” as an explanation to a trick without any metal involved, you know?

If you’re willing to learn, this is the right account for you. My specialty is making money online over Amazon FBA and I teach the method that made me a millionaire.

If this is a model you wanna try out, I got all the resources you need. Welcome to the tribe!

Unpopular opinion: You NEED to curb some of your friends.

“But that’s disloyal”
“But they were there for me”
“But I know them since forever”

Yes, that’s all true.

But your past doesn’t define your future.

If you wanna change and your friends change with you- keep them, they are worth it…

But if you wanna change and they hold you back…

If they can’t handle you upgrading yourself…

They are not friends anymore.

They just became enemies of your new self.

But good news: New friends are waiting for you, especially if you wanna level up by building a business.

node.text:
Time is your most valuable resource - use it wisely!

A tiny lighter won’t keep you warm…

Just as trading valuable hours for a few bucks won’t make you financially free.

But both a lighter and your time are valuable resources…

And you can transform them into other even more valuable resources.

A tiny lighter can start a nice fire, if you use it to burn wood.

The time you have can be converted into value, which earns you more money.

It’s never about the resources you have, it’s about how you use them!
